                            <comment id="15804874" author="ecomar" created="Fri, 6 Jan 2017 16:05:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For the &lt;tt&gt;UnderReplicatedPartitions&lt;/tt&gt; metrics, the Gauge defined inside &lt;tt&gt;ReplicaManager&lt;/tt&gt; needs to be able to make a check like &lt;tt&gt;deleteTopicManager.isTopicQueuedUpForDeletion(topic)&lt;/tt&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The current startup ordering inside &lt;tt&gt;KafkaServer&lt;/tt&gt; has the &lt;tt&gt;ReplicaManager&lt;/tt&gt; start before the &lt;tt&gt;KafkaController&lt;/tt&gt;. &lt;br/&gt;
Could the order be reversed ?&lt;br/&gt;
Else the &lt;tt&gt;ReplicaManager&lt;/tt&gt; could be assigned a &lt;tt&gt;DeletionChecker&lt;/tt&gt; function after the &lt;tt&gt;KafkaController&lt;/tt&gt; has started. This would be minimally disruptive to the current code.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ijuma&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ijuma&quot;&gt;ijuma&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=junrao&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;junrao&quot;&gt;junrao&lt;/a&gt; any preferences ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
